console.settings.index.custom-domains-di: To enable Appwrite's custom domain feature, you have to start your server instance with a public accessible domain name.
Start your Appwrite server container with the _APP_DOMAIN_TARGET environment variable set with a public accessible domain name that resolves to your Appwrite server setup.
The Appwrite server will use your target domain to validate new custom domains and will automatically generate SSL certificates for your new domains using letsencrypt certbot.

Confirm and verify your CNAME record values:
Failed to verify domain, check your DNS records
